		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Bruce Holland Rogers</strong></span> writes fiction and essays full time, and vows to keep it up until he has maxed out all his VISA cards. His work has appeared in <em>Quarterly West</em>, <em>The Magazine of Fantasy &amp; Science Fiction</em>, and <em>Woman&rsquo;s World.</em> He lives in Champaign, Illinois, in an apartment overlooking the tracks of the Illinois Central Railroad.</p><a href="/contributors/bruce-holland-rogers" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
